The former prime minister and OODM leader Raila Odinga yesterday began his charm offensive of the Mount Kenya region at a musicians event hosted by royal media boss S.K Macharia and attended by over 50 elected leaders from the region. So, just what is the genesis of Odinga&rsquo;s love-hate relationship with the mountain, and how impactful are his latest forays into the region ahead of the 2022 polls? KTN senior political reporter Murimi Mwangi interrogates.